{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 200°C. Line a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper.","Place prepared tray onto mixing bowl lid and weigh beetroot and onion onto it. Add carrot, garlic and chilli (optional), then drizzle with 3 tablespoons of the oil and roast for 40 minutes (200°C), turning once during cooking.","Place roasted vegetables, vinegar, sugar, remaining oil, thyme, nutmeg, coriander and salt into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>20 min\/100°C\/speed 2<\/nobr> or until soft. Then blend <strong><nobr>1 min\/speed 4<\/nobr><\/strong><strong>-9, increasing speed gradually from speed 4 to speed 9<\/strong>, until mixture is smooth. If ketchup is thick, add more oil and repeat blending to your desired consistency. Transfer into a sterilised sealable jar and place into refrigerator until ready to serve (see Tips)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["600 g beetroot (approx. 3 beetroots), peeled and cut into pieces (approx. 2-3 cm)","80 g red onion, cut into quarters","1 carrot (approx. 130 g), cut into pieces","1 garlic clove","1 fresh long red chilli, trimmed and cut into thirds (optional)","60 g extra virgin olive oil, plus an extra 3 tbsp for drizzling","90 g apple cider vinegar","30 g coconut sugar","½ tsp dried thyme","½ tsp ground nutmeg","½ tsp ground coriander","½ tsp salt"]}],"id":"r337129","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-aWnsdwrJr6g\/XZafqJ6T7qI\/AAAAAAAAgwk\/EdEp4T_nKKA2-6r7Y_dhlWtshFM0USKGgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_soHGZQNn_RO_eMIq.png","title":"Beetroot ketchup","publishedAt":"2016-08-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"11.8 g","fat":"121.7 g","uom":"per 1 Complete recipe","carbohydrates":"71.4 g","calories":"6133.6 kJ \/ 1460.4 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sterilised sealable jar, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["To save time, you can use fresh, peeled beetroots (and omit step 1). However, the ketchup will be grainy and earthy and will only keep in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.","You can store this ketchup in the refrigerator for up to 3 weeks."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 15m","1"]}